thread.title: Driver dents Camas cop car in coincidental collision
thread.title_full: Driver dents Camas cop car in coincidental collision | OregonLive.com

author: David Greenwald | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Driver dents Camas cop car in coincidental collision
text:
Vancouver resident Daniel Jones, 50, was arrested on Friday night after allegedly running into a police car.
Jones' 2005 Dodge alleged struck Camas police officer Tyson Simmons' vehicle as the officer was assisting in a search for a hit-and-run suspect on Northeast 232nd Ave, the Camas Police Dept. said.
Jones is considered to be the suspect after further investigation, Camas authorities added. His alleged crash into Officer Simmons' car was considered an accident.
Jones was treated at Peace Health SW Medical Center for minor injuries and subsequently booked into Clark County Jail by the Washington State Patrol on a DUI charge.
The State Patrol's investigation continues on the hit-and-run case, and a charge has not been filed. The Clark County Sheriff's office, with Officer Simmons' assistance, conducted the initial hit-and-run investigation.
Officer Simmons was not treated for minor injuries.
